sch:rule.sch:assert:
@calendar indicates one or more systems or calendars to
             which the date represented by the content of this element belongs, but this
              element has no textual content.

sch:rule.sch:report:
When used on a schema description element (like
), the @source attribute
should have only 1 value. (This one has .)

egXML.p:
Looking into the future aeons from the supreme moment of the cosmos, I saw the populations still with all their strength maintaining the
